  "title": "Endoscopy Nurse (Private Clinic / Central / Office Hours)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Profile</strong></p>\n<p>Founded over 25 years ago, we are a fast-growing healthcare group in Singapore with an extensive network spanning primary care, specialist services, diagnostics, and health-screening centres. With a focus on delivering patient-centred care, we want to make quality healthcare accessible, seamless and efficient for individuals, families, and our corporate clients. Employees with us can look forward to a collaborative environment, opportunities for growth, and meaningful involvement in initiatives that shape the future of integrated healthcare.</p>\n<p><strong>Work location: Farrer Park</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Working hours: 5.5 days work week (Mon – Fri and half Sat)</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assess      and admit patients for endoscopy procedures.</li>\n  <li>Prepare      and set up endoscopes and required equipment.</li>\n  <li>Assist      the endoscopist during procedures and monitor patient safety, including      those under sedation.</li>\n  <li>Perform      cannulation, venepuncture, and post-procedure monitoring.</li>\n  <li>Clean,      disinfect, and reprocess endoscopes and other equipment according to      infection-control standards.</li>\n  <li>Maintain      accurate records for equipment usage and reprocessing.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Key Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Min.      Diploma in Nursing with SNB registration</li>\n  <li>Min.      2-3 years’ experience in endoscopy domain as an enrolled nurse or staff nurse</li>\n  <li>Able      to perform cannulation and venepuncture</li>\n  <li>Proficient      in handling endoscopic equipment (OGD, colonoscope, cystoscope).</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of endoscopy procedures, techniques,      and common complications.</li>\n  <li>Competent in operating washer-disinfectors      for endoscope reprocessing.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>📩 Your recruiter: <strong>WhatsApp your CV/resume to Celine</strong> at <strong>8977 7051 </strong>for a quicker response.</p>\n<p>You may also drop your resume via email to celinechan@envirodynamics.com.sg – only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>Celine Chan I Reg. No: R21103433</p>\n<p>EnviroDynamics Solutions Pte Ltd I EA License No.: 12C6285</p>",
